The second likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of clustering algorithms. The third likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper deals with the performance and efficiency of different clustering algorithms. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as clustering is a common unsupervised learning technique.
